In these days of storms and accidents, not only car repair shops make money.
Every day, thousands of cars that have suffered an insured event are towed to a repair shop, where an expert has to estimate the damage and repair costs.
No insurance event is the same, and calculating the cost of parts and labor time can be a long and complicated job.
Manually calculate the cost of repair from 20,000 to 30,000 euros including parts and labor can take two or three hours.
However, with the support of new computer tools, it would be a matter of minutes
That is why almost 100% of experts use this kind of system.
Service providers and solutions for estimating claims and maintenance are dedicated to collecting the information that manufacturers provide to them in order to then develop and offer their customers a useful tool.
In Spain Audatex, from the American group Solera is the leading company; 80% of the evaluation is carried out with its products.
Other companies that compete in the field of valuation tools and development of sector information are GtMotive and Eurotax.
Working with data provided by manufacturers is not easy at all.
According to Eduard Velázquez, sales director of Audatex, 63 manufacturers and importers work in Spain, each providing them with information in a different format.
In addition, the amount of data to be processed is steadily increasing, as more versions, variants and motor solutions have been introduced in the last five years than in the previous fifteen years.
As soon as a new vehicle enters the market, these businesses will start working.
This is a very feverish work, because it is necessary to catalog each of the thousands of parts of the vehicle and determine its price.
In addition, for each model, "intelligent" graphic processing is carried out, where it is possible to "punch out" individual parts of tourist cars.
As for the model with massive sales, the work can be done in a week, if the process is very fast.
As for the minority car, it can take three or four months. Currently, Audatex has complete information on 99.2% of cars sold in Spain.
The most exclusive models they have information about include Porsche, but not, for example, Ferrari or Lamborghini.
In terms of rolling stock in circulation, they exceed 99%.
Audatex has eight centers around the world (Spain, France, Germany, USA, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan) and each of them specializes in specific brands.
The national seat is in Alcobendas (Madrid).
There, more than a hundred technicians (usually mechanics) work simultaneously with three computer screens.
Audatex invests <0xE2><0x82><0xAC>90 million a year in developing these databases.
2.5 million data are added every month and customers receive updates every two days.
Processing this huge stream of information allows businesses to make different uses and deliver different products.
The most common uses focus on repair and maintenance, but there are also country-specific tools to manage spare parts or to calculate the sales or residual value of a car.
The only company that has a guide that informs about the value of used vehicles in Spain is Eurotax.
Audatex does not offer them in our country, but in the United States it does.
With the products offered by Audatex, it is easy to get support that can be used by professionals in the sector.
This business offers ten different tools, with the star product being AudaPlus, a standard premium valuation solution designed for connoisseurs.
It includes cars, motorcycles and light and heavy industrial vehicles.
In addition to the cost of parts, it also includes the repair time estimated by the manufacturer or paint shop.
This tool is paid according to the use for each evaluation.
The highest price is <0xE2><0x82><0xAC>5.75 for customers who use it little, a maximum of ten times a month.
